definition.value: a telangiectasia AE that has telangiectasias covering <10% BSA
a telangiectasia AE that has telangiectasias covering >10% BSA; associated with psychosocial impact
a toxic epidermal necrolysis AE that has skin sloughing covering >=30% BSA with associated symptoms (e.g., erythema, purpura, or epidermal detachment)
an urticaria AE that has urticarial lesions covering <10% BSA; topical intervention indicated
an urticaria AE that has urticarial lesions covering 10 - 30% BSA; oral intervention indicated
an urticaria AE that has urticariallesions covering >30% BSA; IV intervention indicated
an aspiration AE that has altered eating habits; coughing or choking episodes after eating or swallowing; medical intervention indicated (e.g., suction or oxygen)
an aspiration AE that has dyspnea and pneumonia symptoms (e.g., aspiration pneumonia); hospitalization indicated; unable to aliment orally
an atelectasis AE that has symptomatic (e.g., dyspnea, cough); medical intervention indicated (e.g., chest physiotherapy, suctioning); bronchoscopic suctioning
an atelectasis AE that has oxygen indicated; hospitalization or elective operative intervention indicated (e.g., stent, laser)
a chylothorax AE that has symptomatic; thoracentesis or tube drainage indicated
a chylothorax AE that has severe symptoms; elective operative intervention indicated
an epistaxis AE that has moderate symptoms; medical intervention indicated (e.g., nasal packing, cauterization; topical vasoconstrictors)
a Hiccups AE that has  interfering with sleep; limiting self care ADL
a hoarseness AE that has mild or intermittent voice change; fully understandable; self-resolves
a hoarseness AE that has Moderate or persistent voice changes; may require occasional repetition but understandable on telephone; medical evaluation indicated
a hoarseness AE that has severe voice changes including predominantly whispered speech
a hypoxia AE that has decreased oxygen saturation with exercise (e.g., pulse oximeter <88%); intermittent supplemental oxygen
a hypoxia AE that has decreased oxygen saturation at rest (e.g., pulse oximeter <88% or PaO2 <=55 mm Hg)
a hypoxia AE that has life-threatening airway compromise; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., tracheotomy or intubation)
a laryngeal edema AE that has stridor; respiratory distress; hospitalization indicated
a laryngeal edema AE that has life-threatening airway compromise; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., tracheotomy or intubation)
a pleural effusion AE that has symptomatic; intervention indicated (e.g., diuretics or limited therapeutic thoracentesis)
a pleural effusion AE that has symptomatic with respiratory distress and hypoxia; surgical intervention including chest tube or pleurodesis indicated
a pleural hemorrhage AE that has asymptomatic; mild hemorrhage confirmed by thoracentesis
a pleural hemorrhage AE that has symptomatic or associated with pneumothorax; chest tube drainage indicated
a pleural hemorrhage AE that has >1000 ml of blood evacuated; persistent bleeding (150-200 ml/hr for 2 - 4 hr); persistent transfusion indicated; elective operative intervention indicated
a pneumonitis AE that has severe symptoms; limiting self care ADL; oxygen indicated
a pneumonitis AE that has life-threatening respiratory compromise; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., tracheotomy or intubation)
a pneumothorax AE that has symptomatic; intervention indicated (e.g., tube placement without sclerosis)
a pneumothorax AE that has sclerosis and/or operative intervention indicated; hospitalization indicated
a productive cough AE that has occasional/minimal production of sputum with cough
a productive cough AE that has moderate sputum production; limiting instrumental ADL
a productive cough AE that has persistent or copious production of sputum; limiting self care ADL
a pulmonary edema AE that has radiologic findings only; minimal dyspnea on exertion
a pulmonary edema AE that has moderate dyspnea on exertion; medical intervention indicated; limiting instrumental ADL
a pulmonary edema AE that has severe dyspnea or dyspnea at rest; oxygen indicated; limiting self care ADL
a pulmonary edema AE that has life-threatening respiratory compromise; urgent intervention or intubation with ventilatory support indicated
a pulmonary fibrosis AE that has mild hypoxemia; radiologic pulmonary fibrosis <25% of lung volume
a pulmonary fibrosis AE that has moderate hypoxemia; evidence of pulmonary hypertension; radiographic pulmonary fibrosis 25 - 50%
a pulmonary fibrosis AE that has severe hypoxemia; evidence of right-sided heart failure; radiographic pulmonary fibrosis >50 - 75%

a pulmonary fibrosis AE that has life-threatening consequences (e.g., hemodynamic/pulmonary complications); intubation with ventilatory support indicated; radiographic pulmonary fibrosis >75% with severe honeycombing
a pulmonary hypertension AE that has minimal dyspnea; findings on physical exam or other evaluation
a pulmonary hypertension AE that has moderate dyspnea, cough; requiring evaluation by cardiac catheterization and medical intervention
a pulmonary hypertension AE that has severe symptoms, associated with hypoxemia, right heart failure; oxygen indicated
a pulmonary hypertension AE that has life-threatening airway consequences; urgent intervention indicated (e.g., tracheotomy or intubation)
a sinus disorder AE that has asymptomatic mucosal crusting; blood-tinged secretions
a sinus disorder AE that has symptomatic stenosis or edema/narrowing interfering with airflow; limiting instrumental ADL
a sinus disorder AE that has stenosis with significant nasal obstruction; limiting self care ADL
a sinus disorder AE that has necrosis of soft tissue or bone; urgent operative intervention indicated
